#   STATUS-002: `be status` ignores only the sub's own `.gitignore` — needs hierarchical (cwd→$HOME) compounding

`be status:<sub>/` floods with `unk` for paths the repo-root `.gitignore` should exclude (`build-*/`, `*.o`, `CMakeFiles/`, …): the relayed sub-scan `IGNOLoad`s only the SUBMODULE's own `.gitignore`, which `abc` lacks, so the parent's patterns never reach the sub's paths. Bare `be` collapses a sub to one summary row (no flood) — that's the "intermittent". Fix: hierarchical `.gitignore` resolution — load every `.gitignore` from the classified path's directory UP to `$HOME` (or `/` if outside `$HOME`) and COMPOUND them, crossing submodule boundaries, the way nested git ignores stack. NO hardcoded directory names. See [Sniff].

##  Input

### Context
 -  Repro (deterministic; same on PATH `be` and a fresh build — NOT skew): build
    the `abc` sub (makes `abc/build-debug/{CMakeCache.txt,*.o,…}`), then
    `be status:abc/` → ~15 `unk abc/build-debug/...` rows.
 -  `be status:<sub>/` relays into the sub's worktree; its `SNIFFOpen`/`IGNOLoad`
    reads only the SUB's own `.gitignore` (absent for `abc`), so the repo-root
    `.gitignore` never governs the sub's paths.
 -  Bare `be` collapses the sub to one summary row → no flood (the "intermittent").
 -  POST-020 (`8c7f5f3a`) REFUTED: `sniff/SNIFF.c`/`CLASS.c`/`dog/git/IGNO.c`/
    `ULOG.c` are byte-identical to parent `d8fec51a`; the bug is pre-existing /
    structural (since submodule projector recursion), not a regression.
 -  The repo-root `.gitignore` already lists every flooded pattern — it just
    isn't consulted from inside the sub.

### Goals
 -  Hierarchical `.gitignore`: classifying a path loads every `.gitignore` from
    its directory up to `$HOME` (or `/` if not under `$HOME`) and COMPOUNDS them
    (git precedence: nearer/deeper rules add or override; `!` negation honored).
 -  The chain CROSSES submodule boundaries, so a parent repo's `.gitignore`
    governs nested sub paths — this is what fixes the `abc/build-debug` flood.
 -  No hardcoded dir names; `build`/`Corpus`/etc. are excluded ONLY because the
    real `.gitignore`s in the chain list them.

### Constraints
 -  ROLL BACK the prior stop-gap (unconditional `build*/`/`Corpus/` ignore in
    `IGNOMatch`): `Corpus` is not special — restore pattern-only matching.
 -  Honor git pattern semantics (anchoring, dir-only trailing `/`, `!` negation,
    precedence) across the compounded chain.
 -  Terminate the walk at `$HOME` (or `/`); cache the chain per directory so the
    status walk doesn't reload `.gitignore`s for every leaf.

##  WIP

### Design decisions
 -  REJECTED (the prior worker's landed-in-tree fix, to be rolled back):
    `igno_is_build`/`Corpus` special-case in `IGNOMatch` — a hardcoded dir
    blacklist, not ignore resolution.
 -  CHOSEN: an `.gitignore` STACK loaded leaf-dir → `$HOME`/`/`; `IGNOMatch`
    consults it nearest-first with git precedence; built once per directory
    (cached), not per leaf.  Localize in `dog/git/IGNO` + the `sniff/SNIFF`
    open/scan that drives it (incl. the `be status:<sub>/` relay).

